{{see|Cherub}}
==English==
===Etymology===
Ultimately from Hebrew [[כרוב]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈʧɛrəb/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl2=cherubim}}

# A winged creature represented in the [[Bible]] as attending on God, later seen as the second highest order of [[angels]], ranked above [[throne]]s and below [[seraph]]im.
# A statue or other depiction of such a being, typically in the form of a winged child.
# (''figurative'') A person, especially a child, seen as being particularly innocent or angelic.

